This paper deals with the challenges of highly-mobile millimeter wave (mmWave) systems, which are related to information theory (IT) and networking (NI). The proposed solution involves the use of deep learning (LG) to predict beamforming vectors, which is a common application of artificial intelligence (AI) in wireless communications. Finally, the paper specifically mentions the use of large antenna arrays, which is a characteristic of mmWave systems and falls under the category of multimedia (MM).
